This film is a tutorial introduction to the problems of computer vision It begins with a motivation of why knowledge is important to vision Knowledge sources that humans take for granted are shown to be critically important in our understanding of what we see The film then explains the necessary elements in a vision system, be it computer vision or human vision This is illustrated by showing humans who use these elements to interpret images The end of the film gives some detail about the ARGOS image understanding system [Rubin. S.M., "Natural Scene Recognition Using I.oeus Search," CGIP 13. 1960] T'he following is a brief overview of the two main points covered by the film the importance of knowledge sources and the basic elements of an image understanding system.